# Slide 1
;The Mozilla Project launched at Netscape on March 31, 1998, to offer choice to users and drive innovation on the Web.
Ri Mozilla nimasamaj xtz'uk ruma Netscape ri 31 q'ij chi re ri rox rik' ri juna' 1998, akuchi' k'o niya' chi kiwäch ri winaqi' chuqa' nitikirisäx ri tz'ukuj pan Ajk'amaya'l.


# Slide 2
;Proudly non-profit, Mozilla makes products like Firefox with a mission to keep the power of the Web in the hands of users everywhere.
Mozilla nuna' ri' ruma chi jun moloj ri man rutzeqelb'en ta ch'akoj, ri yerunük' taq tikojil achi'el Firefox, akuchi' k'o ri taqel rutaqanem chi ri winaqi' chijun ruwach'ulew tik'oje' kuchuq'a' pa Ajk'amaya'l.


# Slide 3. "The New York Times" is the proper name of an English publication and should not be translated.
;More than 10,000 contributors expressed their support for our mission by paying for a full-page ad in <cite>The New York Times</cite> on the day Firefox 1.0 launched in 2004.
Ri q'ij toq xqelesaj Firefox 1.0 pa 2004, jotöl chi re ri 10 xo'il to'onela' xkito' ri taqel qataqanem rik'in ri xkitöj jun rutzijol ri rumejon jun tz'aqät ruxaq ruwuj <cite>The New York Times</cite>.


# Slide 4
;Today Mozilla has contributors on every continent, including Antarctica (where Firefox is used by 80% of people).
Mozilla e k'o ruto'onela' pa ronojel ri taq setul, achi'el pa Riqi' (akuchi' ri 80% ruwinaq nikokisaj Firefox).


